<li id="cite_note-38"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cancer arising at the junction between the esophagus and stomach is often classified as <a href="/wiki/Stomach_cancer" title="Stomach cancer">stomach cancer</a>, as in <a href="/wiki/ICD-10" title="ICD-10">ICD-10</a>. See: <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://apps.who.int/classifications/icd10/browse/2015/en#/C16">"C16 - Malignant neoplasm of the stomach"</a>. <i>ICD-10 Version: 2015</i>. World Health Organization<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">14 November</span> 2014</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEsophageal+cancer&amp;rft.atitle=C16+-+Malignant+neoplasm+of+the+stomach&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fapps.who.int%2Fclassifications%2Ficd10%2Fbrowse%2F2015%2Fen%23%2FC16&amp;rft.jtitle=ICD-10+Version%3A+2015&amp;rft.pub=World+Health+Organization&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
